subject: Track and Field
lead_paragraph: Chanelle Price of Pennsylvania set a girls’ national high school record for the 500-meter run of 1 minute 10.30 seconds Saturday in the New Balance Games at the Armory Track and Field Center in Upper Manhattan. Liliya Shobukhova of Russia won the women’s elite mile in 4:31.90 and Alycia Williams took the women’s 400 in 53.33 seconds, the fastest times in the world this season.
